package.name: sdo
package.description: Service Data Objects (SDOs) enable PHP applications to work with data from different sources (like a database query, an XML file, or a spreadsheet) using a single interface.

release.notes: Improved reporting of Schema and XML parse errors (libxml2 errors surfaced in an XML Data Access Service SDO_DAS_XML_ParserException). Various bug fixes, including PECL bugs 6002 and 6006. Support for XML Schema 'nillable'. Support to build and run against PHP 6.0 (only with unicode semantics off).

This is the first release of SDO for PHP. It contains the core SDO extension and two Data Access Services: an XML DAS written in C and a Relational DAS to work with relational databases, which is written in PHP and uses PDO. The SDO extension requires a recent version of PHP 5.1. It has been tested on both 5.1.0b2 and 5.1.0b3. The core SDO extension and XML DAS work with 5.1.0b2. The Relational DAS requires PHP 5.1.0b3.
Now includes support for DB2 on both Windows and Linux as well as MySQL. Added some tests for the XML DAS.

This release fixes a number of bugs: - The XML DAS now throws a more meaningful exception when the xsd or xml file is not found - The interface to SDO_DAS_DataFactory::addPropertyToType has changed and the previous interface is deprecated - The interface to SDO_DAS_DataFactory::addProperty now supports the setting of default values - The unit tests for the XML DAS have been added to - The Relational DAS adapts to whether PDO constants are using old-style PDO_* or new-style PDO::* - The Relational DAS contains a workaround for a problem with PDO_Statement::RowCount and ODBC driver - Some SDO_DAS_ChangeSummary* constants, which were probably only used by the Relational DAS, have been changed

This release adds a small number of new features: - The Relational DAS now supports nulls: an SQL NULL in the database is represented as a PHP null in the data object and vice versa - The important SDO classes all support toString() - The SDO_DataObject class now supports clone()

Improved reporting of Schema and XML parse errors (libxml2 errors surfaced in an XML Data Access Service SDO_DAS_XML_ParserException). Various bug fixes, including PECL bugs 6002 and 6006. Support for XML Schema 'nillable'. Support to build and run against PHP 6.0 (only with unicode semantics off).
